Again I spent a lot of time calculating. My first idea was Nxg6 because I assumed he will take my knight and I will win... But then I did see a better move for black, Kg7 and I would most likely have sacrificed my knight for a pawn and lost my advantage in the game. Then I found a better one: 
25. Nxf7  Then if ...Kg7, a suggestion like this follows (or a quicker mate):
26. Rxe6 Rxf7 27. Qxg6  Kf8 28. Qh6  Rg7 29. Rf6  Ke7 30. Qxg7  
So I felt very comfortable about Nxf7 , actually this being a winning move for me. 25... Kg8 is a quick loss for black and taking back with the rook is also a loss by losing heavy material, as the rest of the game shows
